## Performance Tips

### Minimize Database Queries

**Bad:**
```csharp
foreach (var todo in todos)
{
    var user = _db.Users.Find(todo.UserId); // N+1 query!
}
```

**Good:**
```csharp
var todos = _db.TodoItems
    .Include(t => t.User)  // Single join
    .ToList();
```

### Use AsNoTracking for Read-Only Queries

```csharp
var todos = _db.TodoItems
    .AsNoTracking()  // Faster, no change tracking
    .ToList();
```

### Add Response Caching

```csharp
[ResponseCache(Duration = 60)]
public IActionResult Stats()
{
    // Expensive query
}
```

### Database Indexing

In a migration:
```csharp
migrationBuilder.CreateIndex(
    name: "IX_TodoItems_IsComplete",
    table: "TodoItems",
    column: "IsComplete");
```

